JOHANNESBURG – The Public Servants Association (PSA) says former Steinhoff CEO Markus Jooste repeatedly lied to investors, tax authorities, and regulators. The association says it’s been reviewing internal Steinhoff documents. It received the material after approaching Steinhoff’s Stellenbosch headquarters last week, demanding full financial disclosure. READ: Steinhoff scandal points to major gaps in stopping unethical corporate behaviour The documents include minutes of board meetings and other articles dating back to 2002. Assets managers and pensioners were unnerved last month when the retailers share price plunged by more than 80-percent following fraud allegations. eNCA